TY  - JOUR
AU  - Emery, Logan P
T1  - Market dominance in the digital age
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfaf025
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 29
IS  - 4
SP  - 1219
EP  - 1258
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - I document that the network structure of the online economy significantly contributes to rising industry concentration. Firms that are central in the online economy benefit more from increased economies of scale, decreased search costs, and network effects resulting from digitalization. Industries with firms that are more central become more concentrated and central firms have larger increases in market share. These results are driven by firms’ ability to generate revenue, as evidenced by central firms earning higher risk-adjusted returns and having more positive earnings surprises. Centrality is also associated with increasing productivity, but profitability only increases for central firms in business-to-consumer industries.
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfaf025
ER  - 




