TY  - JOUR
AU  - Nguyen, Tu
AU  - Suardi, Sandy
AU  - Zhao, Jing
T1  - Industry tournament incentives and the US financial systemic risk
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfaf026
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 29
IS  - 4
SP  - 1259
EP  - 1302
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Motivated by Coles, Li, and Wang (2020)’s prediction that industry tournament incentives are linked to heightened risk-seeking behavior, we examine whether these incentives contribute positively to systemic risk. Using a measure of systemic risk that captures the cross-sectional tail dependency between the US financial system and individual financial institutions, we find that the external pay gap is positively related to an institution’s contribution to systemic risk. Consistent with our expectation, industry tournament incentives are positively associated with individual financial institutions’ stock return volatility, Value at Risk, and crash risk, thus indirectly contributing to systemic risk due to financial institutions’ inherent interconnectedness. More interestingly, the external pay gap is positively related to an institution’s financial industry beta and encourages systemically risky activities, suggesting an important impact channel through institutions’ undertaking correlated activities.
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfaf026
ER  - 




